      <Section id="intro" title="Tổng quan" themeTag="Intro">
        <p>
          Một trong những điểm hấp dẫn nhất của LLM Wiki: không cần code, không cần server,
          không cần embedding infrastructure để bắt đầu. Một folder, một text editor, và
          Claude là tất cả những gì cần thiết để có working wiki trong 30 phút.
        </p>
        <p>
          Deep dive này là hướng dẫn thực hành: từng bước setup, đầy đủ prompt templates,
          5 use cases với ví dụ cụ thể, và tất cả common mistakes để tránh.
        </p>

        <ReportImage
          src="https://datasciencedojo.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/LLM-Wiki-by-Andrej-Karpahty.png"
          alt="LLM Wiki concept illustration: raw documents on left, wiki entity pages in middle, user querying on right"
          caption="LLM Wiki pattern: raw sources (immutable) → LLM compilation → structured wiki (persistent) → efficient queries."
          source="https://datasciencedojo.com/blog/llm-wiki-tutorial/"
          sourceLabel="Data Science Dojo"
          bordered={true}
        />
      </Section>

      <Section id="setup" title="Setup & First Run" themeTag="Setup">

        <Technique id="t1" title="1. Setup 30 phút — Từ Zero đến Working Wiki" tid="1" location="Data Science Dojo Tutorial + MindStudio Guide">
          <WhyImportant>
            <strong>Threshold to start là gần như zero.</strong> Không có npm install, không có
            Docker, không có API keys cần configure. Chỉ cần folder + Claude.
          </WhyImportant>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Bước 1: Tạo folder structure" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Terminal" lang="bash" code={`# Tạo wiki folder
mkdir -p ~/my-wiki/raw
mkdir -p ~/my-wiki/wiki

# Hoặc tên cụ thể theo topic
mkdir -p ~/ai-research-wiki/raw
mkdir -p ~/ai-research-wiki/wiki`} />

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Bước 2: Tạo CLAUDE.md schema" />
          <CodeBlock caption="~/my-wiki/CLAUDE.md" lang="markdown">
            <Fragment is:raw>{`# My Wiki Schema

## Purpose
[Mô tả mục đích wiki này — vd: "AI research knowledge base" hoặc "Product team knowledge"]

## Directory Structure
- raw/ — immutable source documents (PDFs, articles, notes). NEVER modify.
- wiki/ — LLM-generated entity pages. You own this layer.
- wiki/index.md — catalog of all pages. Update after every ingest.
- wiki/log.md — chronological operation log. Append-only.
- CLAUDE.md — this file (schema and workflows).

## Entity Page Format
\`\`\`markdown
# [Entity Name]
**Type**: Concept | Person | Project | Library | Decision | Event
**Summary**: One sentence (no pronouns — must be standalone).
**Tags**: #tag1 #tag2
**Sources**: [[raw/filename.pdf]]
**Confidence**: 0.XX (N sources, last confirmed YYYY-MM-DD)
**Last Updated**: YYYY-MM-DD

---

## Overview
2-3 paragraph explanation.

## Key Properties
- Specific, verifiable claim 1
- Specific, verifiable claim 2

## Relationships
- **depends_on**: [[Entity A]] — why
- **contradicts**: [[Entity B]] — what they disagree on

## Open Questions
- What's still unclear?
\`\`\`

## Workflows

### Ingest
When I say "ingest [file]":
1. Read source from raw/
2. List entities found → wait for my OK before writing
3. Create/update entity pages
4. Update wiki/index.md
5. Append to wiki/log.md: "## [DATE] ingest | [title]"

### Query
When I ask a question:
1. Read wiki/index.md → find relevant pages
2. Read those pages → synthesize with citations
3. If answer is valuable → offer to file as new wiki page

### Lint (run every ~20 new pages)
Check: contradictions, orphan pages, stale confidence, missing pages.
Report first. Fix only with my permission.
`}</Fragment>
          </CodeBlock>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Bước 3: Install Obsidian (optional nhưng recommended)" />
          <Diagram>{`
1. Download Obsidian từ obsidian.md (free)
2. Launch → "Open folder as vault" → chọn wiki/
3. Press Cmd/Ctrl+G → Graph View
   (visualize connections giữa entity pages)
4. Install Web Clipper extension trong Chrome/Firefox
   (save web articles → raw/ as markdown)
          `}</Diagram>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Bước 4: Install Claude Code (nếu muốn terminal)" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Terminal" lang="bash" code={`# Install Node.js first: nodejs.org
npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code

# Navigate to wiki folder + launch
cd ~/my-wiki
claude`} />

          <Callout type="success">
            <strong>30 phút breakdown:</strong> Tạo folders (2 min) → Copy CLAUDE.md template
            (5 min) → Tìm và download 5 PDFs về topic bạn quan tâm (10 min) → Paste ingest
            prompt vào Claude (5 min) → Open Obsidian, view graph (3 min) → Done!
          </Callout>
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t2" title="2. First Ingest — Khi có sources đầu tiên" tid="2" location="Data Science Dojo Tutorial">
          <WhyImportant>
            <strong>First ingest đặt nền móng cho tất cả.</strong> 5 sources đầu tiên về cùng
            một topic tạo ra dense graph với nhiều connections. 5 sources random thì graph sẽ
            sparse và ít hữu ích hơn.
          </WhyImportant>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Chọn sources đầu tiên — Tips" />
          <Diagram>{`
Good starting set (5 sources):
  ✅ Cùng domain/topic
  ✅ Xây dựng trên nhau (sequential, not parallel)
  ✅ Mix: foundational + recent
  ✅ Ví dụ AI research: Attention (2017) → BERT (2018) → GPT-3 (2020) → Foundation Models (2021) → RLHF (2022)

Bad starting set:
  ❌ 5 topics hoàn toàn khác nhau
  ❌ 5 sources trùng lặp (same info)
  ❌ Mix quá nhiều media types (video transcript + PDF + code + article)
          `}</Diagram>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="First ingest prompt (Claude.ai)" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Paste vào Claude.ai với PDFs attached" lang="markdown" code={`You are maintaining my research wiki. I'm attaching [N] sources on [TOPIC].

Please read all sources, then:

1. Identify all key entities across the sources (concepts, people, systems, methods).
   List them first — I'll confirm before you write pages.

2. For each confirmed entity, create one markdown file using this format:
   [paste format from CLAUDE.md]

3. Add [[wiki-links]] connecting related concepts between pages.

4. Note any contradictions or disagreements between sources.

5. Create wiki/index.md listing all pages with one-line summaries.

6. Create wiki/log.md with:
   ## [2026-04-20] ingest | [list of sources]
   Created: [page list]
   Flags: [any contradictions found]

After all pages are created, give me a brief summary:
- Total pages created
- Key connections discovered
- Any contradictions found`} />

          <Subheading level="h4" text="First ingest prompt (Claude Code)" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Trong Claude Code terminal" lang="markdown" code={`I've added 5 papers to my raw/ folder:
- raw/attention-2017.pdf
- raw/bert-2018.pdf
- raw/gpt3-2020.pdf
- raw/foundation-models-2021.pdf
- raw/rlhf-2022.pdf

Please ingest all of them following the CLAUDE.md workflow.
Read each file, create entity pages in wiki/, update index.md, and log.md.`} />

          <ReportImage
            src="https://datasciencedojo.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Entity-Pages-Created.png"
            alt="Claude Code output showing entity pages being created during wiki ingest"
            caption="Claude Code tạo entity pages sau khi ingest 5 papers. Mỗi page là một concept với wiki-links đến related concepts."
            source="https://datasciencedojo.com/blog/llm-wiki-tutorial/"
            sourceLabel="Data Science Dojo Tutorial"
            bordered={true}
          />
        </Technique>
      </Section>

      <Section id="workflows" title="Ongoing Workflows" themeTag="Workflow">

        <Technique id="t3" title="3. Daily Workflow — Thêm sources và query" tid="3" location="Karpathy + MindStudio Guide">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Daily routine (5-10 phút/ngày)" />
          <Diagram>{`
Sáng (2 min):
  → Open Claude Code trong wiki/
  → "What did I add to the wiki this week? Any open questions?"
  → Get context summary từ log.md

Trong ngày:
  → Gặp article/paper thú vị → save bằng Web Clipper → tự động vào raw/
  → Gặp câu hỏi → hỏi wiki trước khi Google

Cuối ngày (5 min):
  → "Ingest [article tôi vừa đọc]"
  → "File the insights from today's work as wiki/crystals/[date].md"
          `}</Diagram>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Query patterns hàng ngày" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Daily query examples" lang="markdown" code={`# Trước khi viết bài/report:
"What do I know about [topic]? Summarize all relevant wiki pages."

# Khi gặp term không quen:
"Does my wiki have a page on [term]? If yes, what does it say?"

# Khi cần so sánh:
"Based on my wiki, compare [A] vs [B] on dimensions: [X, Y, Z]"

# Gap finding:
"What are the biggest gaps in my wiki on [topic]?
What sources should I read next?"

# Weekly synthesis:
"Generate a one-page summary of everything I've learned this week
based on wiki/log.md and recent wiki pages."`} />
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t4" title="4. Research Workflow — Deep dive vào topic mới" tid="4" location="Karpathy's described use case">
          <WhyImportant>
            <strong>Research wiki là use case Karpathy design cho.</strong> Thay vì đọc 20 papers
            và forget 80% sau 2 tuần, mỗi paper được compiled vào wiki — knowledge cộng dồn
            thực sự.
          </WhyImportant>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="6-week research workflow" />
          <Diagram>{`
Week 1: Foundation
  → Collect 10-15 foundational papers vào raw/
  → Ingest all → initial wiki (30-40 entity pages)
  → Identify: what are the 5 core concepts?

Week 2-3: Deep dive
  → Ingest papers theo từng sub-topic
  → Query + file insights ("What I found: X contradicts Y")
  → Graph view trong Obsidian → identify clusters

Week 4: Synthesis
  → "Synthesize current understanding of [topic] as a structured essay"
  → File as wiki/synthesis/[topic]-overview.md
  → Identify remaining gaps

Week 5: Gap filling
  → Research identified gaps → new sources → ingest
  → Run lint → fix contradictions

Week 6: Output
  → "Based on my wiki, write [blog post / paper outline / presentation outline]"
  → Wiki is ready to cite in your actual output
          `}</Diagram>
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t5" title="5. Team Workflow — Shared Knowledge Base" tid="5" location="LLM Wiki v2 — Multi-agent section">
          <WhyImportant>
            <strong>Internal wikis maintained by humans fail because maintenance is drudgery.</strong>
            LLM Wiki flips this: LLM does maintenance, humans provide direction. For teams,
            this can replace Confluence/Notion maintenance that nobody actually does.
          </WhyImportant>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Team setup" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Team wiki structure" lang="bash" code={`team-wiki/
├── CLAUDE.md                # Shared schema (in git, reviewed by team)
├── raw/
│   ├── shared/              # Team-curated sources (PRs, RFCs, meeting notes)
│   └── personal/[name]/     # Individual contributions
├── wiki/
│   ├── shared/              # Shared entity pages
│   │   ├── index.md
│   │   └── log.md
│   └── personal/[name]/     # Personal working notes
└── scripts/
    └── sync.sh              # Merge personal → shared (manual trigger)`} />

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Governance cho team wiki" />
          <DataTable
            variant="compare"
            richCells
            headers={['What', 'Who decides', 'How']}
            rows={[
              ['Schema updates', 'Tech lead + review', 'PR vào CLAUDE.md'],
              ['Ingest shared sources', 'Anyone', 'Drop vào raw/shared/'],
              ['Create shared pages', 'Anyone', 'Ingest → LLM creates'],
              ['Merge personal → shared', 'Author', 'Manual trigger'],
              ['Contradiction resolution', 'Domain owner', 'Lint flags → discussion'],
              ['Archive stale content', 'Tech lead quarterly', 'Lint report → decision'],
            ]}
          />
        </Technique>
      </Section>

      <Section id="usecases" title="Use Cases — 5 Contexts" themeTag="UseCases">

        <Technique id="t6" title="6. Research Wiki — Papers và Articles" tid="6" location="Karpathy gist — Research use case">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Ví dụ: AI Research Wiki" />
          <Diagram>{`
Domain: Large Language Models research
Sources: arXiv papers, blog posts, conference talks

After 3 months:
  → 150+ entity pages: models, concepts, techniques, people
  → 500+ cross-references
  → 20+ synthesis pages (comparisons, timelines)
  → Wiki can answer: "What is the current SOTA on X?"
  → Wiki can generate: "What's missing in my research?"

Karpathy's actual result:
  "~100 articles, ~400,000 words — wiki still navigates efficiently.
   Faster and more accurate for complex queries than RAG pipeline."
          `}</Diagram>

          <Callout type="unique">
            <strong>Tolkien Gateway analogy.</strong> Karpathy: "Think of fan wikis like Tolkien
            Gateway — thousands of interlinked pages covering characters, places, events, built
            by a community of volunteers over years. You could build something like that personally
            as you read, with the LLM doing all the cross-referencing and maintenance."
          </Callout>
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t7" title="7. Book Wiki — Companion Knowledge Base khi đọc" tid="7" location="Karpathy gist — Reading a book use case">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Quy trình đọc sách với LLM Wiki" />
          <Diagram>{`
Trước khi đọc:
  → Create book-specific CLAUDE.md với entity types: Character, Place, Theme, Event

Trong khi đọc (sau mỗi chapter):
  → "Ingest my notes from Chapter [N]: [summary]"
  → LLM creates/updates character pages, plot threads, themes

Sau khi đọc xong:
  → Query: "Summarize the arc of character X across all chapters"
  → Query: "What are the 5 main themes and how they develop?"
  → Query: "Create a timeline of events"

Result:
  → Companion wiki richer hơn Wikipedia (personalized insights)
  → Có thể revisit book sau 1 năm và quiz wiki thay vì reread
          `}</Diagram>

          <CodeBlock caption="Book-specific CLAUDE.md addition" lang="markdown" code={`## Book-specific Entity Types

Character:
  - full_name, role (protagonist/antagonist/supporting)
  - first_appearance (chapter N)
  - key_relationships: [[other characters]]
  - arc: development through chapters

Place:
  - importance, first_mention, events that happened here

Theme:
  - evidence (list of scenes/quotes)
  - development_arc

Event:
  - chapter, participants, consequences, plot_thread`} />
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t8" title="8. Personal Growth Wiki — Journaling có cấu trúc" tid="8" location="Karpathy gist — Personal use case">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Self-knowledge accumulation" />
          <Diagram>{`
Sources:
  → Daily journal entries (raw/journal/YYYY-MM-DD.md)
  → Articles về personal development
  → Podcast/book notes
  → Therapy session notes (filtered for sensitive info)

Entity types:
  → Pattern: behavioral patterns noticed
  → Goal: ongoing goals với progress
  → Insight: realizations about self
  → Challenge: recurring difficulties

After 6 months:
  → "What patterns appear repeatedly in my journal?"
  → "How has my thinking on [topic] evolved?"
  → "What were my top 3 growth areas this year?"

Benefits:
  → LLM không bị overwhelmed bởi one bad day (like human memory)
  → Synthesis qua nhiều months → patterns bạn không tự thấy
  → Annual review: "Summarize my year based on wiki"
          `}</Diagram>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Privacy critical cho personal wiki.</strong> Filter sensitive data trước khi
            ingest. Không để journal entries raw vào wiki chung với công việc.
            Dùng separate vault cho personal + professional.
          </Callout>
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t9" title="9. Business/Team Wiki — Always Current Internal Docs" tid="9" location="Karpathy gist — Business use case">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Vấn đề LLM Wiki giải quyết cho teams" />
          <Diagram>{`
Traditional internal wikis fail because:
  ❌ No one wants to do the maintenance (Confluence graveyards)
  ❌ Knowledge dies in Slack threads
  ❌ Onboarding is "read these 50 docs" (painful)
  ❌ Architecture decisions undocumented

LLM Wiki flips the model:
  ✅ Slack thread export → raw/ → LLM ingests → wiki page
  ✅ Meeting transcript → raw/ → LLM ingests → decision + action pages
  ✅ PR description → raw/ → LLM ingests → system change documented
  ✅ Customer call → raw/ → LLM ingests → product feedback synthesized

Result:
  → Wiki là living document thực sự
  → Onboarding: "Ask the wiki anything about [system]"
  → Architecture decisions có rationale được preserved
          `}</Diagram>

          <CodeBlock caption="Meeting ingest example" lang="markdown" code={`# Drop meeting transcript vào raw/meetings/2026-04-20-arch-review.md
# Then tell Claude:

"Ingest raw/meetings/2026-04-20-arch-review.md

This is a meeting transcript. Extract:
1. DECISIONS: Any explicit decisions made
2. ACTION ITEMS: Assigned tasks (owner, deadline)
3. CONTEXT: Technical context established
4. OPEN QUESTIONS: Unresolved items

Create:
- wiki/decisions/2026-04-20-redis-migration.md (if decision made)
- wiki/people/[owner].md (if new team member mentioned)
- wiki/projects/[project].md (if project discussed)"`} />
        </Technique>
      </Section>

      <Section id="bestpractices" title="Best Practices" themeTag="Best Practices">

        <Technique id="t10" title="10. Common Mistakes — Và Cách Tránh" tid="10" location="Data Science Dojo Tutorial + community experience">
          <WhyImportant>
            <strong>Most wikis fail for predictable, preventable reasons.</strong>
            Biết trước mistakes giúp tránh 90% những vấn đề người dùng mới gặp phải.
          </WhyImportant>

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Top 6 mistakes" />

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 1: Quá nhiều thứ trong 1 page.</strong> Mỗi entity page nên cover
            ĐÚNG 1 concept. Nếu một page bắt đầu cover 2 ideas → split it. Dense single-concept
            pages tạo better links và better answers.
          </Callout>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 2: Không bao giờ chạy lint.</strong> Small errors propagate fast.
            Một wrong claim → linked bởi 3 pages → organized misinformation. Chạy lint sau
            mỗi 20 pages mới.
          </Callout>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 3: Thêm quá nhiều unrelated topics cùng lúc.</strong>
            5 papers về cùng topic → dense, useful graph.
            5 papers về 5 topics khác nhau → sparse, less useful.
            Build depth trước breadth.
          </Callout>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 4: Không file good answers back vào wiki.</strong>
            Nếu Claude synthesize một insightful comparison → file it.
            Nếu bạn discover một connection qua research → file it.
            Explorations mà không được filed thì lost.
          </Callout>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 5: Schema drift.</strong>
            Nếu format của pages drift (mỗi page có structure khác nhau), LLM sẽ
            inconsistent. Update CLAUDE.md ngay khi bạn change format. Treat schema như
            production config.
          </Callout>

          <Callout type="warn">
            <strong>Mistake 6: One giant wiki cho mọi thứ.</strong>
            Separate wikis theo domain work tốt hơn. Một wiki cho research, một cho personal,
            một cho work. Graphs dày hơn và answers chính xác hơn khi wikis focused.
          </Callout>
        </Technique>

        <Technique id="t11" title="11. Ecosystem Tools" tid="11" location="MindStudio + community">
          <Subheading level="h4" text="Tool stack cho LLM Wiki" />
          <DataTable
            variant="compare"
            richCells
            headers={['Tool', 'Role', 'Cost']}
            rows={[
              ['<strong>Claude Code</strong>', 'Primary LLM agent — ingest/query/lint', 'Anthropic subscription'],
              ['<strong>Obsidian</strong>', 'Visual wiki browser, graph view, backlinks', 'Free (local)'],
              ['<strong>Obsidian Web Clipper</strong>', 'Save web articles → raw/ as markdown', 'Free'],
              ['<code>rank-bm25</code>', 'BM25 search index (>200 pages)', 'Free (Python package)'],
              ['<code>sentence-transformers</code>', 'Local vector embeddings', 'Free (local)'],
              ['FAISS', 'Vector similarity search', 'Free (Meta OSS)'],
              ['MindStudio', 'Wrap wiki in shareable web UI cho team', 'Paid'],
              ['Git', 'Version control cho wiki/ + CLAUDE.md', 'Free'],
            ]}
          />

          <Subheading level="h4" text="Git integration" />
          <CodeBlock caption="Git setup cho wiki" lang="bash" code={`cd ~/my-wiki
git init
echo "raw/" >> .gitignore  # raw sources thường quá lớn để version control
git add CLAUDE.md wiki/
git commit -m "Initial wiki with 5 papers"

# Weekly commit:
git add wiki/
git commit -m "Week of $(date +%Y-%m-%d): added N pages on [topic]"

# Benefit: có thể rollback nếu LLM tạo bad content trong lint/bulk ops`} />

          <Callout type="success">
